Dear Mariyaiya,

*Thank you. This is a precise and complete answer — exactly what the FSD 
requires.*

EmpCommon is now fully resolved. The origin (login module reading 
PO_Para.EmpMasterComm per DivCode), the logic (Y = True = 
Cry_Purchase_Req, else False = Cry_PR_KSL), and the five confirmed 
divisions (Saranya, Armstrong, Cheran, Skaat, VTS) are all documented. 
The flag is database-driven with no hardcoding anywhere in the form — 
this is the right architecture and it carries cleanly into SPINRISE.

*Please update the FSD in three places:*

In Section 5 (Business Logic), add a sub-section on the EmpCommon flag: 
state that it is set at login by reading PO_Para.EmpMasterComm for the 
active DivCode, document the Y/N logic, and cross-reference Section 7.

In Section 7 (Print / Report Architecture), add the list of five 
divisions currently using Cry_Purchase_Req, and add a SPINRISE migration 
note: the dual Crystal report branching is replaced by a single 
server-side PDF generator with a division-level template selection 
parameter in PO_Para. New customer onboarding must set EmpMasterComm 
correctly before the PR print will work.

In Section 11 (Customer Variation Register), add an entry recording the 
Cry_Purchase_Req vs Cry_PR_KSL division split with the current five 
divisions listed, and document the SPINRISE resolution.

One item remains on your side before the FSD can be submitted for the 
full IST review chain. I asked in my earlier mail whether the Rate field 
override logic in Section 5.2 — which reads from IN_TRNHEAD and 
IN_TRNTAIL where TC = 1 — is live and active in practice, or dead code. 
Muthuvel and Palanivel have confirmed that TC is not used in the PO 
module at all. If that is correct, this query should never execute. 
Please check in the VB6 code whether this rate override is actually 
triggered in any live customer scenario, or whether it is a legacy query 
that was written but never used. One of three outcomes is possible: it 
is dead code and should be removed, it is active cross-module logic 
reading from the Store module, or it executes but produces no visible 
effect because TC = 1 records do not exist in the PO context. The answer 
must be in Section 5 before the FSD goes to Muthuvel for IST sign-off.

Update the document with the three EmpCommon additions and the TC rate 
override finding, then resubmit.

Regards,
T. Mani

