            with the selected item for procurement purposes. This
            information is displayed based on the applicable department
            and is currently available only in the transaction print,
            not in other reports. This feature helps customers track
            item selection within their workflow. </p>
          <p><b>Suggestions : PR Line Items needed Item code + Machine. </b></p>
          <p><br>
            •Confirm: Is po_para.PRapprovalstatus display-only, or does
            it gate any operation? </p>
          <p>Ans:- One of the ease of use point, it display in the
            Transactions Form Side up window to know current status of
            the PR, otherwise every time qureies PR Status to know the
            status. </p>
